2::0::
2::0::Bring the body of a dead noble back to life.  There is a 50% chance
2::0::of success for each attempt.
2::0::
2::0::If successful, the resurrected noble will be brought back to life and
2::0::stack beneath the priest.  The resurrected noble's loyalties will
2::0::remain the same as they were at the time of the noble's death.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Preparatory ritual~[9303]
2::0::-------------------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9303
2::0::Time:   three days
2::0::
2::0::The priest completes a holy ritual which assures future religious
2::0::acts of success.  Many skills within the Religion category have a
2::0::50% chance of failure; completing 9303 before use of these skills
2::0::removes the possibility of their failure.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Last rites~[9304]
2::0::-----------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9304 <dead noble>
2::0::Time:   ten days
2::0::
2::0::Attempt to commend a dead noble's body to its final resting place.
2::0::This prayer prevents the body from being resurrected or fouled in
2::0::any way.
2::0::
2::0::Must be performed in a temple.  The dead noble's body need not
2::0::be present to execute this prayer.  Last rites has a 50% chance
2::0::of success.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Remove blessing from soldiers~[9305]
2::0::------------------------------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9305 <target>
2::0::Time:   ten days
2::0::
2::0::Remove the blessing from all of the target's blessed soldiers.
2::0::Any blessed soldiers possessed by the target will be converted
2::0::back to regular soldiers.
2::0::
2::0::If a target is not specified, the target will default to the priest.
2::0::The target must be present in the priest's location.
2::0::
2::0::This prayer has a 50% chance of success.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Survive fatal wound~[9501]
2::0::--------------------------
2::0::Usage:   implicit
2::0::
2::0::Knowledge of 9501 confers the ability for a noble to survive
2::0::a wound which would be normally be fatal.  If the noble's
2::0::health reaches zero, either through combat or by other harm,
2::0::instead of dying the noble will be restored to full health.
2::0::
2::0::Once the skill has been used, it is forgotten.  To survive
2::0::a second fatal would, the noble would have to spend another
2::0::Noble Point and study for three weeks to learn 9501 again.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Sailing~[9502]
2::0::--------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9502 <direction or location>
2::0::Or:     SAIL <direction or location>
2::0::
2::0::Requires:  character must be ship's captain
2::0::Time:      varies with route taken
2::0::
2::0::Pilot a ship in the given direction, or to the specified
2::0::location.  If a location is specified, there must be a direct
2::0::route to it from the current location of the ship.
2::0::
2::0::Compass points may be abbreviated:  N, S, E, W.
2::0::
2::0::The character issuing the Pilot ship order must occupy the
2::0::first position inside the ship (the character must be the
2::0::captain of the ship).
2::0::
2::0::The captain must have a crew to assist in the handling of the
2::0::ship.  Galleys require fourteen sailors as oarsmen to row the ship.
2::0::Roundships require at least eight sailors to man the ship's rigging.
2::0::
2::0::        ship            crew
2::0::        ----            ----
2::0::        galley          14 sailors
2::0::        roundship       8 sailors
2::0::
2::0::If the required number of crew are not available, travel is still
2::0::possible, but will take an extra day for each hand the crew is short.
2::0::
2::0::For example, a galley with only 10 men at the oars will take four
2::0::extra days to travel across an ocean route.  A roundship with no
2::0::sailors at all would take eight extra days to traverse a route.
2::0::
2::0::Galleys perform equally well regardless of wind conditions.
2::0::Roundships may be becalmed and unable to travel.  In the presence
2::0::of favorable wind they will travel across ocean routes in half
2::0::the rated time.
2::0::
2::0::Overloaded ships do not sail well.  They may take longer than
2::0::expected to travel across routes, and are almost certain to
2::0::capsize and sink in a storm.  Captains should be careful not
2::0::to leave port in a vessel carrying too much cargo.
2::0::
2::0::For convenience, one may use the SAIL order rather than "USE 9502".
2::0::Knowledge of Pilot ship [9502] is still required, however.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Shipbuilding~[9503]
2::0::-------------------
2::0::Usage:     BUILD galley "Name of ship"
2::0::or         BUILD roundship "Name of ship"
2::0::
2::0::Requires:  at least three workers [11]
2::0::	   50 wood [77] for a galley, 100 wood for a roundship
2::0::
2::0::Time:      250 worker-days for a galley, 500 for a roundship
2::0::
2::0::To begin construction of a ship, the shipbuilder should unstack from
2::0::beneath other characters and issue one of the BUILD orders.  One-fifth
2::0::of the lumber is required to start construction.  The rest is deducted
2::0::as progress on the ship is made (the second fifth at 20% completion,
2::0::the third fifth at 40% completion, etc.)
2::0::
2::0::The shipbuilder and his workers will be placed inside the new ship.
2::0::
2::0::As soon as the required number of worker-days has been invested in
2::0::construction, the ship will be christened and declared seaworthy.
2::0::
2::0::To resume construction of a partially completed ship, first enter the
2::0::ship, then issue the either "build galley" or "build roundship".
2::0::
2::0::Ships may only be built in locations with a passable route to an
2::0::ocean, such as a port city.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Bird spy~[9504]
2::0::---------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9504 <direction or destination>
2::0::Time:   three days
2::0::
2::0::The beastmaster employs the use of a bird to fly into an nearby
2::0::location and return with a report.  A direction may be given, as
2::0::with the MOVE order, or a destination may be specified.  The
2::0::destination may be any sublocation in the same province, or
2::0::any neighboring location.
2::0::
2::0::For example, a bird could fly from inside a castle in a province to
2::0::spy on a tower in a city in the same province.  The bird could spy
2::0::on a neighboring province, but not enter sublocations in the
2::0::neighboring province.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Fight to the death~[9505]
2::0::-------------------------
2::0::Usage:   USE 9505 <break-point>
2::0::Time:    0 days
2::0::
2::0::Normally a side will break when its offensive plus defensive total
2::0::falls by 50% or more.  Knowledge of 9505 allows a leader to override
2::0::this default break point and set it to any value between 0 and 100.
2::0::
2::0::A break point of zero means that a side will not break, and will
2::0::fight until the last man has been killed.  A break point of 100
2::0::means the side will break immediately after the first volley of
2::0::attacks is launched.
2::0::
2::0::    Default setting:      USE 9505 50
2::0::    Fight to the death:   USE 9505 0
2::0::    Break at 30:          USE 9505 30
2::0::
2::0::Note that "break at 30%" means that the side will break when its
2::0::offensive plus defensive total falls to 30% of its original value.
2::0::
2::0::During combat, only the stack leader's setting for 9505 is checked.
2::0::9505 works both for attacking and defending stacks.
2::0::
2::0::Note that prisoners may still be taken from a side fighting to the
2::0::death, as wounded nobles may be too weak to resist being taken
2::0::captive.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Capture beasts in battle~[9506]
2::0::-------------------------------
2::0::Usage:  automatic when needed
2::0::
2::0::Wild animals will ordinarily fight to the death.  Nobles who enter
2::0::combat with these creatures must either kill them, or be killed
2::0::themselves.
2::0::
2::0::Beastmasters with knowledge of 9506, however, can capture rather
2::0::than kill these wild animals.  The skilled beastmaster will lure
2::0::the animal into a trap, or carefully engage it until the beast
2::0::becomes exhausted.
2::0::
2::0::9506 is used automatically whenever the character attacks (or is
2::0::attacked by) one of the following wild beasts:
2::0::
2::0::    centaur~[271]
2::0::    minotaur~[272]
2::0::    giant spider~[278]
2::0::    rat~[279]
2::0::    lion~[280]
2::0::    giant bird~[281]
2::0::    giant lizard~[282]
2::0::    chimera~[284]
2::0::    harpie~[285]
2::0::    dragon~[286]
2::0::    gorgon~[288]
2::0::    wolf~[289]
2::0::
2::0::To capture wild beasts, the noble should ATTACK them.  A regular
2::0::combat will occur, and the noble's stack may suffer casualties.
2::0::9506 does not change the progress of battle, or the outcome if
2::0::the noble loses.
2::0::
2::0::If the noble is victorious, however, instead of the wild beasts
2::0::being destroyed, their unit wrapper will be disbanded, and the
2::0::beast items will be added to the noble's inventory.
2::0::
2::0::The beastmaster need not be the stack leader for 9506 to work.
2::0::However, the stack leader will always receive the booty.
2::0::
2::0::For example:  suppose Osswid is stacked over Feasel, and Feasel
2::0::knows 9506, but Osswid doesn't.  Beasts will be captured in
2::0::battle, but they will go into Osswid's inventory, not Feasel's.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Use beasts in battle~[9507]
2::0::---------------------------
2::0::Usage:  automatic when needed
2::0::
2::0::This skill grants the beastmaster the ability to control animals
2::0::in battle.  Any wild animals in the possession of the beastmaster
2::0::will be treated as additional fighters.
2::0::
2::0::For example, a character with 10 soldiers [12] and one lion [280]
2::0::who did not know 9507 would only use the soldiers in battle.
2::0::However, a beastmaster with knowledge of 9507 would also employ
2::0::the lion in combat.
2::0::
2::0::Only the beasts directly possessed by the beastmaster will aid
2::0::combat.  Animals owned by units which do not possess knowledge
2::0::of 9507 will not be used in battle.
2::0::
2::0::The following animals may be used in combat:
2::0::
2::0::    nazgul~[55]          (80,80,0)
2::0::    centaur~[271]        (30,30,0)
2::0::    minotaur~[272]       (30,5,0)
2::0::    giant spider~[278]   (150,100,0)
2::0::    rat~[279]            (3,3,0)
2::0::    lion~[280]           (100,100,0)
2::0::    giant bird~[281]     (200,150,0)
2::0::    giant lizard~[282]   (30,30,0)
2::0::    chimera~[284]        (130,130,0)
2::0::    harpie~[285]         (80,120,0)
2::0::    dragon~[286]         (500,500,0)
2::0::    gorgon~[288]         (10,20,0)
2::0::    wolf~[289]           (5,5,0)
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Breed beasts~[9508]
2::0::-------------------
2::0::Usage:  BREED <item> <item>
2::0::Time:   seven days
2::0::
2::0::Attempt to breed two animals together to produce an offspring.
2::0::Not all animals produce successful offspring.  Occasionally,
2::0::cross-breeding different beasts will produce strange results.
2::0::
2::0::For example:
2::0::
2::0::	To breed two wild horses together:
2::0::
2::0::		BREED 51 51
2::0::
2::0::	To attempt a cross-breed of a horse and an ox:
2::0::
2::0::		BREED 51 76
2::0::
2::0::Because some animals are often unpredictable and violent, there
2::0::is a small chance that one of the breeding parents will be killed
2::0::in the attempt.
2::0::
2::0::Wild horses [51], riding horses [52] and warmounts [53] may be used
2::0::interchangably with BREED.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Petty thievery~[9509]
2::0::---------------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9509
2::0::Time:   seven days
2::0::
2::0::The skill of the common burglar, 9509 allows a thief to work a
2::0::city for gold.  The thief may pick pockets, steal from merchants
2::0::in the market, enter homes in search of loot, or deceive townsfolk
2::0::into parting with their gold with confidence games.
2::0::
2::0::9509 may only be used in a city, where there are many opportunities
2::0::for the petty thief.  Since reports of thievery tend to make the
2::0::city residents tense and alert, 9509 may only be used once per month
2::0::in each city.
2::0::
2::0::A thief will earn between 50 and 150 gold for each successful use of
2::0::9509.  There is a 5% chance that instead of obtaining gold, the thief
2::0::will be caught and beaten, and receive a 5-15 point health loss.
2::0::
2::0::The amount of gold the thief obtains from the city is deducted from
2::0::the city's tax base for the month.
2::0::
2::0::Cities which have recently been pillaged offer no opportunities for
2::0::petty thievery, as the residents have already been stripped of their
2::0::valuables, and are wary of strangers.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Bribe noble~[9515]
2::0::------------------
2::0::Usage:   BRIBE <target> <gold> [flag]
2::0::Time:    seven days
2::0::
2::0::Offer a character gold in an attempt to win their service.  The
2::0::amount must be at least 250 gold, or the receiving noble will not
2::0::consider it a serious offer.
2::0::
2::0::Nobles with oathbound loyalty ignore bribes.  They may accept the
2::0::gift, but they will not renounce loyalty to their lord.
2::0::
2::0::Nobles with contract loyalty will consider the bribe if it meets
2::0::or exceeds their current loyalty rating.  For example, a noble of
2::0::loyalty contract-750 would ignore any bribe of less than 750 gold.
2::0::
2::0::Nobles with fear loyalty, or nobles not sworn to any lord, will
2::0::seriously consider any bribe of at least 250 gold.
2::0::
2::0::If the receiving noble considers the bribe, there is a 33% chance
2::0::they will renounce loyalty to their current lord, and swear fealty
2::0::to the bribing character.  There is also a chance that they will
2::0::report the bribe or pocket it for themselves.  In some cases they
2::0::may even renounce loyalty to their lord, but not swear fealty to
2::0::the briber, instead choosing to go off on their own.
2::0::
2::0::Characters who are successfully bribed will have loyalty contract-250
2::0::to the bribing character.  If flag is 1, and the bribe attempt is
2::0::successful, the bribed character will stack with the briber.
2::0::
2::0::Bribes will be refused by characters who have already switched
2::0::lords during the month because of bribery.  For example, suppose
2::0::Osswid successfully bribes Feasel, and Feasel swears loyalty to
2::0::Osswid.  Later that turn, if Procrustes attempts to bribe Feasel,
2::0::Feasel will refuse to accept the bribe.
2::0::
2::0::Examples:
2::0::
2::0::    bribe 5499 750	# Offer [5499] 750 gold to switch factions.
2::0::			# If successful, [5499] will not stack with the
2::0::			# briber.
2::0::
2::0::    bribe 3409 300 1	# Offer [3409] 300 gold to switch factions.
2::0::			# If successful, [3409] will stack with the briber.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Catch wild horses~[9517]
2::0::------------------------
2::0::Usage:  CATCH  [number of horses]  [days]
2::0::Time:   as given or necessary
2::0::
2::0::Attempt to catch any wild horses found roaming the plains or pastures.
2::0::Each day the noble will have a 25% chance of catching a wild horse,
2::0::if any can be found.  Up to three horses may be caught per month in a
2::0::plains province.
2::0::
2::0::A unit must know the Catch wild horses [9517] subskill of Beastmastery [123]
2::0::in order to catch horses.
2::0::
2::0::Examples:
2::0::
2::0::    catch        # catch as many horses as possible
2::0::    catch 1      # stop after catching 1 wild horse
2::0::    catch 0 10   # try to catch horses for 10 days
2::0::    catch 1 10   # stop after catching 1 wild horse, or 10 days, whichever
2::0::                 # comes first
2::0::
2::0::In all cases, horse-catching ceases when no more horses can be found
2::0::roaming in the location.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Determine inventory of character~[9519]
2::0::---------------------------------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9519 <character>
2::0::Time:   seven days
2::0::
2::0::Sneakily learn the contents of the specified character's inventory.
2::0::The spy must be in the same location as the target.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Determine skills of character~[9520]
2::0::------------------------------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9520 <character>
2::0::Time:   seven days
2::0::
2::0::Sneakily learn what skills the specified character possesses by
2::0::crafty observation and spying.
2::0::
2::0::The spy must be in the same location as the target.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Determine character's lord~[9521]
2::0::---------------------------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9521 <character>
2::0::Time:   seven days
2::0::
2::0::Reveals what player the specified character is sworn to, unless
2::0::the target character is concealing its identity.  The spy must be
2::0::in the same location as the target.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Learn of richest nearby noble~[9522]
2::0::------------------------------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9522
2::0::Time:   seven days
2::0::
2::0::Must be used in an inn.  The character will chat with the local
2::0::patrons of the inn, inquiring as to the recent comings and goings
2::0::of other nearby characters, paying special attention to clues
2::0::which would indicate the presence of wealthy units.
2::0::
2::0::Use of 9522 will reveal the identity of the richest noble within
2::0::three provinces of the inn.  Any character with less than 500
2::0::gold is not considered wealthy, and is ignored by 9522.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Torture prisoner~[9523]
2::0::-----------------------
2::0::Usage:  TORTURE <prisoner>
2::0::Time:   seven days
2::0::
2::0::Torture is the practice of inflicting pain on a captive prisoner in
2::0::order to extract information against the victim's will.
2::0::
2::0::Torture will attempt to learn what faction the prisoner belongs to.
2::0::Each torture attempt inflicts a 50 point health loss on the prisoner.
2::0::
2::0::The chance of success depends on the prisoner's loyalty:
2::0::
2::0::	loyalty		chance
2::0::	-------		------
2::0::	oath-2		  0%
2::0::	oath-1		 10%
2::0::	contract	 50%
2::0::	fear		100%
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Train wild horse to riding horse~[9529]
2::0::---------------------------------------
2::0::Usage:     MAKE 52
2::0::
2::0::Requires:  one wild horse [51]
2::0::Produces:  one riding horse [52]
2::0::
2::0::Time:      seven days
2::0::
2::0::Wild horses are first broken to saddle, then trained to respect
2::0::and obey whatever riders they may serve.  Once broken, riding
2::0::horses become too timid and docile to be of any use in battle.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Train wild horse to warmount~[9530]
2::0::-----------------------------------
2::0::Usage:     MAKE 53
2::0::
2::0::Requires:  one wild horse [51]
2::0::Produces:  one warmount [53]
2::0::
2::0::Time:      fourteen days
2::0::
2::0::Unlike riding horses, war horses must not be broken.  The war horse
2::0::should be trained without destroying any of its spirit.  A warmount
2::0::is also be taught much more than a simple riding animal, as it
2::0::must know how to defend itself and its rider and to remain calm
2::0::in the most frightening situations.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Persuade oathbound noble~[9536]
2::0::-------------------------------
2::0::Usage:   USE 9536 <target> [flag]
2::0::Time:    seven days
2::0::
2::0::Attempt to persuade an oathbound noble to defect.  There is
2::0::only a chance of success when used on oath-1 nobles.  Oath-2
2::0::nobles will not leave their lord under any circumstances.
2::0::
2::0::9536 costs 25 gold per use, to pay for gifts, fine meals, handsome
2::0::clothing, and other props useful in the persuasion attempt.
2::0::
2::0::Each seven day use yields a 2% chance of success.
2::0::
2::0::If flag is 1, and the persuasion attempt is successful, the target
2::0::character will stack with the persuading character.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Raise peasant mob~[9537]
2::0::------------------------
2::0::
2::0::Usage:  RAISE
2::0::Time:   seven days
2::0::
2::0::The noble gives an impassioned speech, rousing peasants and causing
2::0::them to gather into a crowd.  New peasant crowds will set their GUARD
2::0::flag to protect their homes from pillaging.
2::0::
2::0::Peasant mobs may be formed in provinces and cities.  Only one crowd
2::0::may be raised per location.  Only when the raised mob is later killed,
2::0::or if the peasants return to their homes, may another mob be raised
2::0::there.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Rally peasant mob~[9538]
2::0::------------------------
2::0::Usage:  RALLY <mob>
2::0::Time:   seven days
2::0::
2::0::Deliver a fiery speech to an existing crowd of peasants, causing them
2::0::to stack with the noble.  They will remain with the noble for three
2::0::months.  The mob must be specified as an argument to RALLY.
2::0::
2::0::Use of 9538 on a mob already stacked with the noble will renew the
2::0::peasants' enthusiasm, and add an additional three months to the time
2::0::they will remain stacked, to a maximum of five months.
2::0::
2::0::Mobs stacked with the noble may not be given any orders, but will
2::0::participate in any combat the noble encounters.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Incite mob violence~[9539]
2::0::--------------------------
2::0::
2::0::Usage:  INCITE <mob> <target>
2::0::Time:   seven days
2::0::
2::0::Speak out against the target in such as a way as to inspire
2::0::public hatred and ire.  The target will be made to seem a
2::0::malicious influence responsibile for all of the common man's
2::0::troubles.
2::0::
2::0::An existing crowd of peasants must be specified as the first
2::0::argument, and the target of their violence as the second.
2::0::The mob may not already be stacked under another noble who
2::0::has rallied it.
2::0::
2::0::There is a 50% chance that the mob will be roused to attack
2::0::the target.
2::0::
2::0::There is also a 33% chance that patrons in any local inns will
2::0::learn that the noble is trying to incite a mob to violence
2::0::against the target.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Construct battering ram~[9540]
2::0::------------------------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9540
2::0::
2::0::Requires:  three wood [77]
2::0::           one iron [79]
2::0::           three workers [11]
2::0::
2::0::Produces:  one battering ram [60]
2::0::
2::0::Time:      fourteen days
2::0::
2::0::The craftsman constructs a battering ram by selecting a large,
2::0::heavy tree trunk, sharpening the end somewhat and plating it
2::0::with iron, and then suspending it in a movable wooden frame
2::0::such that it may be swung back and forth against walls or gates.
2::0::
2::0::The frame receives an iron plated roof to protect the operators
2::0::from boiling oil or pitch, rocks, or other missile weapons hurled
2::0::down upon them by the enemy.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Construct catapult~[9541]
2::0::-------------------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9541
2::0::
2::0::Requires:  three wood [77]
2::0::           three workers [11]
2::0::
2::0::Produces:  one catapult [61]
2::0::
2::0::Time:      fourteen days
2::0::
2::0::The engineer directs the construction of a wheeled wooden frame
2::0::containing a mechanism to supply stress to the end of a long
2::0::wooden pole.  The pole contains a basket which may be loaded
2::0::with stones or other missiles to be hurled against the enemy's
2::0::walls, or over them.  A winch to lower the pole and a release
2::0::mechanism finish the siege engine.
2::0::
2::0::Catapults are sometimes loaded with the bodies of the enemy's
2::0::dead and hurled over their walls, to dishearten the besieged and
2::0::spread disease amongst them.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Construct siege tower~[9542]
2::0::----------------------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9542
2::0::
2::0::Requires:  three wood [77]
2::0::           three leather [80]
2::0::           three workers [11]
2::0::
2::0::Produces:  one seige tower [62]
2::0::
2::0::Time:      fourteen days
2::0::
2::0::The engineer directs three workers to build a wooden tower,
2::0::covered with treated leather skins or iron plating to protect
2::0::the tower from burning.  The tower contains several ladders
2::0::and a platform from which soldiers may attack.
2::0::
2::0::In battle, the tower is wheeled up against an enemy's walls
2::0::and used by attacking soldiers to match the height of the
2::0::defenders.  The attackers may then climb from the tower onto
2::0::the walls.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Extract venom from ratspider~[9549]
2::0::-----------------------------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9549
2::0::
2::0::Required:  one ratspider [81]
2::0::Produces:  one ratspider venom [63]
2::0::Time:      seven days
2::0::
2::0::The alchemist performs a delicate operation to extract the
2::0::highly poisonous ratspider venom.
2::0::
2::0::The top of the ratspider's head is removed by inserting a sharp
2::0::knife above the head joint and twisting.  Two glands, from which
2::0::the ratspider venom is later extracted, are removed from behind
2::0::the mandible.
2::0::
2::0::Risk is minimized by taking extreme care when handling the
2::0::ratspider.  The ratspider is killed in the process. 
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Make potion of slavery~[9550]
2::0::-----------------------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9550
2::0::
2::0::Required:  one ratspider venom [63]
2::0::Time:      seven days
2::0::
2::0::The alchemist brews a potion which, when ingested by a character,
2::0::causes that character to become a servant of the alchemist.
2::0::The unfortunate noble will swear fealty to the alchemist and
2::0::promise to do his bidding.
2::0::
2::0::The rare and highly poisonous ratspider venom is used in the
2::0::preparation of this potion.  Upon completion, the new potion
2::0::will be added to the alchemist's inventory.  The potion will,
2::0::of course, be unlabeled.
2::0::
2::0::A character wishing to drink the potion should specify it
2::0::to the USE order.  For instance, to drink potion [601], issue
2::0::the order:  USE 601.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Brew healing potion~[9551]
2::0::--------------------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9551
2::0::
2::0::Required:  avinia leaf [65]
2::0::Time:      seven days
2::0::
2::0::The alchemist brews a potion of healing.  Any character
2::0::ingesting the potion will be immediately healed of any
2::0::wounds or other maladies.
2::0::
2::0::Upon completion, the potion will be added to the alchemist's
2::0::inventory.  The potion's label will not reveal its purpose.
2::0::
2::0::A character wishing to drink the potion should specify it
2::0::to the USE order.  For instance, to drink potion [602], issue
2::0::the order:  USE 602.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Brew potion of death~[9552]
2::0::---------------------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9552
2::0::
2::0::Required:  lana bark [64]
2::0::Time:      ten days
2::0::
2::0::The alchemist brews a potion which will cause instant death
2::0::to any character which drinks it.
2::0::
2::0::Upon completion, the potion will be added to the alchemist's
2::0::inventory.  The potion's label will not reveal its sinister
2::0::purpose.
2::0::
2::0::A character wishing to drink the potion should specify it
2::0::to the USE order.  For instance, to drink potion [603], issue
2::0::the order:  USE 603.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Add ram to galley~[9554]
2::0::------------------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9554
2::0::
2::0::Requires:  three workers [11]
2::0::           3 wood [77]
2::0::           1 iron [79]
2::0::
2::0::Time:      10 days
2::0::
2::0::A galley fitted with a ram is a most effective ocean fighting
2::0::vessel.  The oars permit the ship to be maneuvered in battle,
2::0::regardless of wind conditions.  The ram allows a galley to crush
2::0::the sides of enemy ships.
2::0::
2::0::To use this skill, the character must enter the galley and issue
2::0::USE 9554.  The galley will be fitted with an iron-tipped ram.
2::0::The character need not be in control of the ship in order to
2::0::perform the modification.
2::0::
2::0::Rams may not be added to roundships or unfinished galleys.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Conceal identity of trader~[9562]
2::0::---------------------------------
2::0::Usage:  BUY  <item> <qty> <price> <have-left> 1
2::0::        SELL <item> <qty> <price> <have-left> 1
2::0::
2::0::This skill allows a trader to conceal his identity when
2::0::dealing with a market.  By working through middlemen and
2::0::employing shady contacts, the trader will not reveal his
2::0::identity to the other party to his transaction, or to the
2::0::market at large.
2::0::
2::0::To use this skill, the trader should supply a "1" flag as
2::0::the fifth argument to the BUY or SELL command.  Note that
2::0::The first four arguments must be specified; use "0" for
2::0::have-left if it is to be left as the default.
2::0::
2::0::For example, to conceal one's identity when selling 10
2::0::pots for 2 gold each, issue the order:
2::0::
2::0::	sell 95 10 2 0 1
2::0::
2::0::If the conceal trade flag is supplied, but the character
2::0::does not know 9562, the BUY or SELL order will fail.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Mine iron~[9563]
2::0::----------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9563
2::0::
2::0::Requires:  ten workers
2::0::Time:      7 days
2::0::
2::0::Iron is widely used in the making of weapons and armor.  It
2::0::is a required component of many of the weaponsmithing skill
2::0::uses, and is also used for applying a metal tip to galley
2::0::rams and battering rams.  An iron roof provides a protective
2::0::cover for siege towers.
2::0::
2::0::The character must be in a mine shaft to USE 9563.  The mine's
2::0::monthly yield of iron will be obtained.  Once mined, no further
2::0::iron can be mined until the next month.
2::0::
2::0::Use of this skill will cause the mine shaft to become one-third
2::0::of a level deeper.
2::0::
2::0::The quantity of iron obtained will vary with the depth of the
2::0::shaft.  The largest deposits of iron are usually found in
2::0::shallow mines.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Mine gold~[9564]
2::0::----------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9564
2::0::
2::0::Requires:  ten workers
2::0::Time:      7 days
2::0::
2::0::Gold is widely accepted as a currency in Olympia.  Its
2::0::scarcity lends gold a high value, but it is not so rare
2::0::that it cannot be used in the everyday exchange of goods.
2::0::It has a high value, but weighs little, and thus is easy to
2::0::carry.  Gold is also readily assayable to guarantee its value.
2::0::
2::0::The character must be in a mine shaft to USE 9564.  The mine's
2::0::monthly yield of gold will be obtained.  Once mined, no further
2::0::gold can be mined until the next month.
2::0::
2::0::Use of this skill will cause the mine shaft to become one-third
2::0::of a level deeper.
2::0::
2::0::The quantity of gold obtained will vary with the depth of the
2::0::shaft.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Mine mithril~[9565]
2::0::-------------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9565
2::0::
2::0::Requires:  ten workers
2::0::Time:      7 days
2::0::
2::0::Mithril is a magical metal used in the by the ancient
2::0::elf-lords to construct their bright, fearsome weapons.
2::0::Today mithril is the component of some rare construction
2::0::skills.
2::0::
2::0::The character must be in a mine shaft to USE 9565.  The mine's
2::0::monthly yield of mithril will be obtained.  Once mined, no
2::0::further mithril can be mined until the next month.
2::0::
2::0::Use of this skill will cause the mine shaft to become one-third
2::0::of a level deeper.
2::0::
2::0::The quantity of mithril obtained will vary with the depth of the
2::0::shaft.  Mithril is usually found only in very deep mines.  As
2::0::the dangers of poison gasses or collapse of the mine shaft increase
2::0::with depth, mithril mining tends to be risky.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Stone quarrying~[9566]
2::0::----------------------
2::0::Usage:     QUARRY [number of stones] [days]
2::0::Requires:  at least one worker
2::0::
2::0::Building stone is used in the construction of temples, castles and
2::0::towers.  Up to 50 stone may be removed from mountain provinces or
2::0::rocky hills each month, or up to ten stone from desert provinces.
2::0::
2::0::Each worker will cut and prepare one building stone [78] per day.
2::0::
2::0::Examples:
2::0::
2::0::    quarry         # cut as much building stone as possible
2::0::    quarry 25      # stop after cutting 25 stone
2::0::    quarry 0 5     # quarry stone for five days
2::0::    quarry 25 5    # stop after five days, or 25 stone, whichever
2::0::                   # comes first
2::0::
2::0::In all cases, quarrying will cease as soon as the supply of ready stone
2::0::in the province has been exhausted.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Harvest lumber~[9568]
2::0::---------------------
2::0::Usage:     WOOD [number] [days]
2::0::Time:      as given or necessary
2::0::Requires:  at least one worker [11]
2::0::
2::0::Workers enter the forest and select trees which are suitable for felling
2::0::and sawing.  Lumber is used in the construction of ships, buildings and
2::0::some weapons.  Timber is also used to support the roofs of mine shafts.
2::0::
2::0::Must be used in a forest province.  Forests generate 30 wood [77] each
2::0::month.
2::0::
2::0::Examples:
2::0::
2::0::    wood         # obtain as much wood as possible
2::0::    wood 25      # stop after getting 25 wood
2::0::    wood 0 5     # cut timber for five days
2::0::    wood 25 5    # stop after five days, or 25 wood, whichever
2::0::                 # comes first
2::0::
2::0::In all cases, timber cutting will cease as soon as the forest's supply
2::0::of wood for the month has been exhausted.
2::0::
2::0::WOOD is an alias for COLLECT 77.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Harvest yew~[9569]
2::0::------------------
2::0::Usage:     YEW [number] [days]
2::0::Times:     as given or necessary
2::0::Requires:  at least one worker [11]
2::0::
2::0::Workers enter a yew grove and select yew trees which are suitable for
2::0::collection.  Yew is used in the making of longbows.
2::0::
2::0::Must be used in a yew grove.  Yew groves generate 5 yew [68] each month.
2::0::
2::0::Examples:
2::0::
2::0::    yew         # obtain as much yew as possible
2::0::    yew 1       # stop after getting 1 wood
2::0::    yew 0 4     # cut yew for four days
2::0::
2::0::In all cases, yew harvesting will cease as soon as the grove's supply
2::0::of yew for the month has been exhausted.
2::0::
2::0::YEW is an alias for COLLECT 68.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Defense~[9570]
2::0::--------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9570
2::0::
2::0::Time:   seven days
2::0::
2::0::The noble will spend time and effort practicing skills and
2::0::techniques of personal and combat defense.  Each use of 9570
2::0::raises the noble's defense rating by one point.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Record skill on scroll~[9573]
2::0::-----------------------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9573 <skill>
2::0::
2::0::Requires:  blank scroll [84]
2::0::Time:      seven or more days
2::0::
2::0::Record the given skill on a blank scroll.  The blank scroll will be
2::0::consumed, and a new unique scroll will be produced.  The new scroll
2::0::will allow one character to learn the skill.
2::0::
2::0::Example:
2::0::
2::0::    USE 9573 nnnn     # make a one-time study scroll for skill nnnn
2::0::
2::0::Magical skills may not be scribed with this skill.
2::0::
2::0::The skill must be known in order to be written.  The character will
2::0::still know the skill after writing it.
2::0::
2::0::This skill requires as much time as the recorded skill takes to learn.
2::0::Writing a skill which requires two weeks of study to learn will take
2::0::two weeks.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Sneak into structure~[9574]
2::0::---------------------------
2::0::Usage:  SNEAK [building or ship]
2::0::Time:   three days
2::0::
2::0::The character will sneak into the specified building or ship.
2::0::Once inside, other occupants of the structure will see the
2::0::character in their location reports, unless the unit employs
2::0::additional methods of concealment.  Occupants will not see the
2::0::character enter, however.
2::0::
2::0::To exit the structure by the same means, use SNEAK with no
2::0::arguments.
2::0::
2::0::The unit must be alone in order to sneak into and out of buildings
2::0::or ships.  It may not be stacked with any other characters, or
2::0::possess any followers, such as peasants, soldiers, workers, etc.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Archery~[9579]
2::0::--------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9579
2::0::Time:   seven days
2::0::
2::0::Learning 9579 gives the noble a +50 missile attack rating.
2::0::
2::0::Use of 9579 will cause the noble to spend time and effort
2::0::practicing archery further.  Every seven-day use will
2::0::increase the noble's missile rating by one point.
2::0::
2::0::Knowledge of Archery also allows the noble to train archers and
2::0::elite archers, via the TRAIN order.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Swordplay~[9580]
2::0::----------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9580
2::0::
2::0::Time:   seven days
2::0::
2::0::Use of 9580 will cause the noble to spend time and effort practicing
2::0::swordplay, for use in personal combat.  Every seven-day use will
2::0::increase the noble's attack rating by one point.
2::0::
2::0::Knowledge of Swordplay also allows the noble to train swordsmen,
2::0::knights, and elite guards, via the TRAIN order.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Weaponsmithing~[9581]
2::0::---------------------
2::0::Usage:  MAKE  <item> <days>
2::0::Time:   as given
2::0::
2::0::Weapons and armor are required for the training of some kinds of
2::0::fighters.  Archers require longbows, for instance, elite guard
2::0::require plate armor, etc.
2::0::
2::0::Weapons and armor are made with the MAKE command.  The following
2::0::weapons and armor may be produced:
2::0::
2::0::    num   item           material
2::0::    ---   ----           --------
2::0::     72   longbow        yew [68]
2::0::     73   plate armor    iron [79]
2::0::     74   longsword      iron [79]
2::0::     75   pike           wood [77]
2::0::     85   crossbow       wood [77]
2::0::
2::0::One unit of the input material may turned into one of the desired
2::0::items each day.  For example, MAKE 72 2 would spend two days turning
2::0::two yew [68] into two longbows [72].
2::0::
2::0::See the MAKE command for further information.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Fishing~[9582]
2::0::--------------
2::0::Usage:     FISH [number of fish] [days]
2::0::Requires:  at least one sailor
2::0::
2::0::Unit must be on a ship on the ocean in order to fish.  Each day
2::0::spent fishing there is a 50% chance that the ship will come across
2::0::a school of fish.  If fish are found, each sailor will produce one
2::0::fish that day.  Provinces generate 50 fish per month which may be
2::0::obtained by fishing.
2::0::
2::0::Examples:
2::0::
2::0::    fish         # obtain as many fish as possible
2::0::    fish 25      # stop after getting 25 fish
2::0::    fish 0 5     # fish for five days
2::0::    fish 25 5    # stop after five days, or 25 fish, whichever
2::0::                 # comes first
2::0::
2::0::In all cases, fishing will cease as soon as the stocks in the ocean
2::0::province have been exhausted.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Collect rare foliage~[9583]
2::0::---------------------------
2::0::Usage:  COLLECT <item> [number] [days]
2::0::Time:   as given or necessary
2::0::
2::0::The noble will seek rare foliage to collect.  See the COLLECT order
2::0::for details on the syntax of the arguments and an explanation of the
2::0::columns in the following table.
2::0::
2::0::The followings kinds of rare foliage may be collected with this skill:
2::0::
2::0::   num  item         who      where            qty  skill  chance
2::0::   ---  ----         ---      -----            ---  -----  ------
2::0::    64  lana bark    noble    circle of trees    3   9583    50%
2::0::    65  avinia leaf  noble    mallorn grove      2   9583    20%
2::0::    66  spiny root   noble    bogs, pits         4   9583    25%
2::0::    66  spiny root   noble    swamps             1   9583    25%
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Collect rare elements~[9584]
2::0::----------------------------
2::0::Usage:  COLLECT <item> [number] [days]
2::0::Time:   as given or necessary
2::0::
2::0::The noble will seek rare elements to collect.  See the COLLECT order
2::0::for details on the syntax of the arguments and an explanation of the
2::0::columns in the following table.
2::0::
2::0::The followings kinds of rare elements may be collected with this skill:
2::0::
2::0::   num  item         who      where          qty  skill  chance
2::0::   ---  ----         ---      -----          ---  -----  ------
2::0::    67  farrenstone  noble    caves            2   9584   100%
2::0::    71  pretus bones noble    sand pits        1   9584   100%
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Summon wild men~[9585]
2::0::----------------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9585
2::0::        MAKE 98 1
2::0::Time:   one day
2::0::
2::0::Wild men, or savages, inhabit remote parts of the world.  Savages
2::0::communicate by beating their drums to indicate calls-to-arms,
2::0::battle challenges, or victory celebrations.
2::0::
2::0::Use of 9585 will attempt to summon wild men with drumbeats, and
2::0::persuade them to stack with the noble.  Savages will remain with
2::0::the noble for 3 months, during which time they will participate
2::0::in any battles the noble fights.
2::0::
2::0::To summon wild men, the noble must first use the MAKE 98 1 order
2::0::to produce a drum [98].  A drum requires 1 mallorn wood [70] to
2::0::produce.  MAKE 98 1 requires knowledge of 9585.
2::0::
2::0::The drum may be used to summon wild men with the USE 9585 order.
2::0::The noble should be in a remote province, preferably surrounded by
2::0::areas uninhabited by other characters.  The noble should allow time
2::0::for the savage men to hear and follow the drumbeats.  Any wild men
2::0::summoned to the province will stack with the noble.
2::0::
2::0::For example:
2::0::
2::0::	make 98 1	# make a drum
2::0::	use 9585	# use the drum to summon the savages
2::0::	wait time 15	# give savages time to arrive and
2::0::			# stack with us
2::0::
2::0::The number of savage units in the world is limited.  If all of the
2::0::available savages have already been summoned, none will come when
2::0::the drum is used.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Persuade wild men to remain~[9586]
2::0::----------------------------------
2::0::Usage:  USE 9586 <savage>
2::0::Time:   seven days
2::0::
2::0::Usage of 9586 will induce a group of wild men to remain stacked with
2::0::the noble that summoned them.  An application of 9586 will add two
2::0::months to the duration the wild men will stay with the noble, to a
2::0::maximum of four months.
2::0::
2::0::The savage unit to be persuaded to remain must be specified as an
2::0::argument to USE 9586.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Harvest mallorn wood~[9587]
2::0::---------------------------
2::0::Usage:    MALLORN [number] [days]
2::0::Time:     as given or necessary
2::0::
2::0::Mallorn groves produce two units of mallorn wood [70] which may be
2::0::harvested each month.
2::0::
2::0::Because of the careful selection required, and the small quantity of
2::0::mallorn which becomes ready to cut each month, a noble works at this
2::0::task alone.  No workers are needed for mallorn wood cutting.
2::0::
2::0::Each day spent using MALLORN gives a 20% chance of obtaining one
2::0::unit of mallorn wood [70].
2::0::
2::0::Examples:
2::0::
2::0::    mallorn         # obtain as much mallorn wood as possible
2::0::    mallorn 2       # stop after getting 2 mallorn wood
2::0::    mallorn 0 5     # cut mallorn wood for five days
2::0::    mallorn 2 5     # stop after five days, or 2 mallorn wood, whichever
2::0::                    # comes first
2::0::
2::0::In all cases, mallorn cutting will cease as soon as the groves's supply
2::0::for the month has been exhausted.
2::0::
2::0::MALLORN is an alias for COLLECT 70.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Harvest opium~[9588]
2::0::--------------------
2::0::Usage:    OPIUM [number] [days]
2::0::Time:     as given or necessary
2::0::
2::0::Poppy fields produce 25 harvestable opium [93] each month.
2::0::A noble using the OPIUM command will collect one unit of opium
2::0::each day.
2::0::
2::0::Examples:
2::0::
2::0::    opium          # obtain as much opium as possible
2::0::    opium 25       # stop after getting 25 opium
2::0::    opium 0 5      # harvest opium for five days
2::0::    opium 25 5     # stop after five days, or 25 opium, whichever
2::0::                   # comes first
2::0::
2::0::In all cases, opium harvesting will cease as soon as the field's supply
2::0::for the month has been exhausted.
2::0::
2::0::OPIUM is an alias for COLLECT 93.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Improve opium production~[9589]
2::0::-------------------------------
2::0::Usage:    USE 9589
2::0::Time:     seven days
2::0::
2::0::Use of 9589 causes the noble to pay special attention to the
2::0::development of a poppy field.  Through appropriate fertilization
2::0::and agressive weed and pest control, the opium production of the
2::0::poppy field will be doubled in the following month, from 25 to 50
2::0::units of opium.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Turn lead into gold~[9590]
2::0::--------------------------
2::0::Usage:     USE 9590 [amount]
2::0::Time:      one week
2::0::Requires:  one farrenstone [67]
2::0::
2::0::Using obscure chemical processes, the Alchemist may turn lead
2::0::into gold.  One unit of farrenstone is required as a catalyst
2::0::for the conversion.
2::0::
2::0::Up to 20 units of lead may be converted with each use of 9590.
2::0::Amount defaults to 20 or all of the lead in the Alchemist's
2::0::inventory, whichever is less.  Each unit of lead yields 10 gold
2::0::after conversion.
2::0::
2::0::
2::0::Conceal faction~[9591]
2::0::----------------------
2::0::Usage:  automatic when necessary
